subSubSection.paragraph:
Head: labrum with V–shaped notch anteriorly (but not as deep as in e.g. 

Hydraena larissae

). Fronto–clypeal suture slightly arcuate, not strongly impressed. Middle of frons moderately densely punctate, lateral portion of frons very densely punctate, as in related species. Occipital ridge well developed. Eyes moderately large, maxillary palpi very long, about twice as long as distance between eyes.
